                "actions": {
                    "value": 2
                },
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>The forge-spurned breathes a cloud of stinging soot, ash, and glowing embers. This can affect either a <span data-pf2-effect-area=\"cone\" data-pf2-distance=\"30\">30-foot cone</span> or a <span data-pf2-effect-area=\"burst\\\" data-pf2-distance=\"20\">20-foot burst</span> centered on the forge-spurned and persists for [[/br 1d4 #rounds]]{1d4 rounds}.</p>\n<p>Each creature that moves into or starts their turn in the area takes [[/r 6d6 #fire]]{6d6 fire damage}, with a <span data-pf2-check=\"reflex\" data-pf2-traits=\"damaging-effect,divine,evocation,fire\" data-pf2-label=\"Forge Breath DC\" data-pf2-dc=\"21\" data-pf2-show-dc=\"gm\">basic Reflex</span> save. A creature that fails its save is also @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Blinded]{Blinded} for 1 minute.</p>\n<p>Creatures within the cloud are @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Concealed]{Concealed}, though not from the forge-spurned.</p>\n<p data-visibility="gm">The forge-spurned can't use Forge Breath again until it has used Inflate Bellows.</p>"
